Step 1. Create The Dashboard

First Launch The EC2 instance by using the instance-setup-script

Login AWS Console -> Search Bar -> CloudWatch -> Dashboards -> Create dashboard -> Dashboard name -> Name -> Create dashboard -> Widget Configuration -> Next -> 
Click On EC2 -> Click On Per-Instance Metrics -> Search The Instance ID



Step 2. Search The Metrices -> After Search Create widget -> Save -> Select The Dashboard -> View in metrics -> Select The Gauge

Select The Below Metrices

CPUUtilization
NetworkIn
NetworkOut
DiskReadBytes
DiskWriteBytes



Step 3. Search The Logs

View in metrics -> Add query -> Logs(Top 10 log groups by incoming events) 
View in metrics -> Add query -> Logs(Top 10 log groups by written bytes) 
